Key technical points (implementation-ready):
- TypeError is a built-in Error subclass used when an operation is applied to a value of an inappropriate type.
- Constructor signature: new TypeError([message]) -> TypeError instance with name 'TypeError' and provided message.
- Common scenarios: accessing properties on null/undefined, calling non-callable values, passing wrong type to API.

